    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0433">
<l>oṉṟumuta lāka veṭṭa ṉiṟuti</l>
<l>yellā veṇṇum pattaṉ muṉvariṟ</l>
<l>kuṟṟiya lukara meyyoṭuṅ keṭumē</l>
<l>muṟṟa viṉvarūu miraṇṭalaṅ kaṭaiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If all the words denoting numbers from <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉṟu</foreign> ' one ' to <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṭṭu</foreign> ' eight '</l>
<l>succeed <foreign xml:lang="ta">pattu</foreign> ' ten ', the overshort <foreign xml:lang="ta">-u</foreign> disappears with [its] con-</l>
<l>sonant ; the empty morph <foreign xml:lang="ta">iṉ</foreign> is inserted ; this [rule] does not ap-</l>
<l>ply to [the numeral] <foreign xml:lang="ta">iraṇṭu</foreign> ' two '.<note place="foot">I.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">pattu + oṉṟu &gt; pat-iṉ-oṉṟu; pattu + mūṉṟu
          &gt; patiṉmūṉṟu...pattu + eṭṭu &gt; patiṉeṭṭu ;</foreign> but <foreign xml:lang="ta">
          paṉṉiraṇṭu,</foreign> cf. the next aphorism.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
